  "description": "<i>The Legend of the Elves</i> is a fantasy point &amp; click graphic adventure about a young elf named Eric, who lives with his family on a small island. One day Eric arrives at home, expecting to be greeted by his parents and younger sibling, only to find the house deserted. He finds a note pinned to the wall with a knife that tells him his family has been kidnapped, and there is a hefty ransom for their return. Eric doesn't have the money to pay the ransom, and sets off on a quest to save his family.<br><br>The interface splits the screen vertically into two sections: the top half shows the current scene from a third-person perspective, and underneath is a panel that shows the items you are currently carrying, as well as six action buttons: &quot;Pick up&quot;, &quot;Talk to&quot;, &quot;Use&quot;, &quot;Give&quot;, &quot;Look at&quot;, and &quot;Throw&quot;.",
